            <p class="govuk-body">
                This notice sets out how we will use your personal data, and your rights. It is made under Articles 13 and/or 14 of the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR).
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                This notice relates to data collected under the Help to Grow: Digital scheme (“the scheme”) run by the UK Government Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (“BEIS”).
            </p>
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="background">Background</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                The Help to Grow: Digital scheme is funded and administered by BEIS. BEIS is the Data Controller. If an external scheme administrator is appointed and, or any of these arrangements change, you will be notified via email. The recipients listed below will be Data Processors for the Help to Grow: Digital scheme.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
               References to “we” and “our” in this Privacy Policy mean BEIS. Any references in this Privacy Policy to “you” or “your” means the Scheme Participant.
            </p>
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="your-data">Your Data</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                We will process the following personal data:
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>First name</li>
                    <li>Surname</li>
                    <li>Email address</li>
                    <li>Phone number</li>
                    <li>Applicant position/role within the SME</li>
                    <li>IP address</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="purpose">Purpose</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                The purpose(s) for which we are processing your personal data is to manage your participation in the Help to Grow: Digital scheme, which includes to assess your eligibility for the scheme, to process your application for and issue you with financial discounts (grant token), to evaluate the performance of the scheme, as well as to provide other information or to contact you from time to time and to update you further on Help to Grow: Digital. We are also processing your personal data to monitor web traffic via web analytics, including IP address and pages visited and interacted with.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Your data may also be used for statistical, research and where it is necessary for the purposes of the prevention, investigation, detection, or prosecution of criminal offences, including fraud.
            </p>
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="legal-basis-of-processing">Legal basis of processing </h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                The legal basis for processing your personal data is Public Task: Processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in BEIS. In this case, to process your participation in the Help to Grow: Digital scheme and related activities, and to contact you regarding any future Help to Grow: Digital scheme updates.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                For marketing and communications purposes, the legal basis for processing your personal data is <strong>Consent:</strong> You consent to us doing so.
