            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="other-data-processing">Other data processing</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Data about your SME, excluding any personal data listed above, will be shared with HMRC in connection with the promotion of the Help to Grow: Digital Scheme. This will enable HMRC to measure the impact of the promotional campaign it intends to run in partnership with the Department for Business, Energy & Industrial Strategy. Data shared with HMRC may include Companies House reference number, VAT number, PAYE number or unique tax reference as well as details of the financial discount you have applied for and received.
            </p>           
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="how-we-protect-your-data-and-keep-it-secure">How we protect your data and keep it secure </h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                We are committed to doing all that we can to keep your data secure. We have set up systems and processes to prevent unauthorised access or disclosure of your data – for example, we protect your data using varying levels of encryption. We also make sure that any third parties that we deal with keep all personal data they process on our behalf secure.
            </p>           
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="recipients">Recipients</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Your personal data will be shared by us with:
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>Any Government department involved in the Help to Grow: Digital Scheme and their delivery partners</li>
                    <li>Scheme Administrator, if appointed, for the administration of the Help to Grow: Digital scheme</li>
                    <li>BEIS Monitoring and evaluation partners (RSM UK Consulting LLP, BiT and NESTA)</li>
                    <li>Matt Hamnett & Associates (MH+A) Ltd for scheme administration support purposes</li>
                    <li>PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) for scheme administration support purposes</li>
                    <li>BEIS marketing and communications delivery partners and third parties (Blueberry Marketing, Kantar Public UK Ltd, Omnicom Media Group UK Ltd T/A Manning Gottlieb OMD), for marketing and communications, supporting discount (grant token) applications and software purchases by the SME applicant, and scheme administration purposes.</li>
                    <li>Registered vendors and key sub-contractors, for marketing and communications, supporting discount (grant token) applications and software purchases by the SME applicant, and for scheme administration purposes (including following up with you if you have applied for a discount (grant token) but not redeemed it). Registered vendors and key sub-contractors are:
                        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                            <li>e-Commerce software: Bigcommerce UK Limited, Comgem Limited, EKM Systems Limited, GOb2b Limited, Kentico Software Limited, Platform 21 Limited (ShopWired)</li>
                            <li>Customer Relationship Management (CRM) software: Esteiro Business Solutions Limited (Gold-Vision), Deskpro Limited, Livepoint Software Solutions Limited (Swiftcase), Zestia Limited (Capsule), Zymplify Limited (Zym)</li>
                            <li>Digital Accounting software: E-Crunch Limited, Intuit Limited, Sage (UK) Limited</li>                    
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>As your personal data will be stored on our IT infrastructure, it will also be shared with our data processors Microsoft and Amazon Web Services</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="recipients">Retention</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Your personal data will be kept by BEIS for the duration of the Help to Grow: Digital Scheme. The scheme will run for three years. Data held for monitoring and evaluation purposes will be held up until the end of the relevant contracts, currently scheduled until March 2025 unless extended. If extended, data held under evaluation partner contracts will be held for 9-12 months after programme end. Our evaluation and monitoring partners will delete your personal data after expiry of the evaluation contract.
            </p>           
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="your-rights">Your rights</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You have the right to request information about how your personal data are processed, and to request a copy of that personal data.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You have the right to request that any inaccuracies in your personal data are rectified without delay.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You have the right to request that any incomplete personal data are completed, including by means of a supplementary statement.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You have the right to request that your personal data are erased if there is no longer a justification for them to be processed.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You have the right in certain circumstances (for example, where accuracy is contested) to request that the processing of your personal data is restricted.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data where it is processed for direct marketing purposes.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You have the right to withdraw consent to the processing of your personal data at any time. If you wish to withdraw your consent, please contact: <a href="mailto:SME.helptogrow@beis.gov.uk">SME.helptogrow@beis.gov.uk</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data.
            </p>
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="where-do-we-process-your-personal-data">Where do we process your personal data? </h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                BEIS and supporting service providers will process your Personal Data to the extent possible in the United Kingdom or the European Economic Area (EEA). Your Personal Data will be retained on servers located in the United Kingdom.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                We will take all steps necessary to ensure that your data is processed and stored in a secure environment, in accordance with our legal obligations. The data that we collect from you may be transferred to, and stored at, a destination outside the European Economic Area (‘EEA'). All suppliers and contractors we use to process data are bound by contract to keep it secure in accordance with UK GDPR.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                As your personal data is stored on the BEIS IT infrastructure and shared with our data processors Microsoft and Amazon Web Services, it may be transferred and stored securely in the UK and EEA. Where your personal data is stored outside the UK and EEA it will be subject to equivalent legal protection through the use of Model Contract Clauses.
            </p>
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="complaints">Complaints</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                If you consider that your personal data has been misused or mishandled, you may make a complaint to the Information Commissioner, who is an independent regulator. The Information Commissioner can be contacted at:
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Information Commissioner's Office
                <br />Wycliffe House
                <br />Water Lane
                <br />Wilmslow
                <br />Cheshire
                <br />SK9 5AF
                <br />Telephone: 0303 123 1113
                <br />Email: <a href="mailto:casework@ico.org.uk">casework@ico.org.uk</a>
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Any complaint to the Information Commissioner is without prejudice to your right to seek redress through the courts.
            </p>
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="contact-details">Contact Details</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                The data controller for your personal data is the Department for Business, Energy & Industrial Strategy (BEIS). You can contact the BEIS Data Protection Officer at:
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
